 experiences of an adolescent and young woman who regarded herself as a committed National Socialist, and whose self-perception, thinking, and daily life were shaped by membership in the female branch of the Hitler Youth, the Bund Deutscher Mädel.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a FA license: uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/free-access-policy uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHistoryxHistorical PeriodsxContemporary HistoryxContemporary History until 1945. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, German. 4aMünchen. 4aNachkriegszeit. 4aNationalsozialismus. 4aZweiter Weltkrieg. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aMunich.  aNational Socialism.  aSecond World War.  apost-war period.1 aKeller, Sven, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1z978311076251808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2015z9783110438635oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831104054840 cprintz978311040485240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110405378zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110405378zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110405378/original  a978-3-11-070098-5 DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  a978-3-11-076251-8 DG Plus DeG Package 2015 Part 1b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2015  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-GOA